The paper proposes a deep learning approach for generating API usage sequences based on natural language queries. This involves understanding the semantics of the query and the associated APIs, which suggests relevance to sub-categories such as software engineering (cs.SE), computational linguistics (cs.CL), and machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the approach utilizes information retrieval models, which relates to sub-categories such as information retrieval (cs.IR) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
